        <h1>Activity 2.2 If Statements</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-4" />

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <h2>Introduction</h2>

        <Presentation>
          <section>
            <h3>Activity 2.2</h3>
            <h4 class="text-skynest-theme">If Statements</h4>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Topics</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Making Decisions</li>
              <li>If Statements</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>Making Decisions</h4>
            <p>
              <b>Programs need to make choices.</b> Sometimes, your code must decide
              what to do based on a condition, like whether someone is old enough
              to drive.
            </p>
            <p class="fragment">
              <b>This kind of decision-making is called selection.</b> It lets your
              program follow different paths depending on what's true.
            </p>
          </section>
          <section>
            <h4>
              The <AstroCode
                code="if"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              /> Statement
            </h4>
            <p>
              An if statement allows your program to check a condition and
              decide whether or not to execute a block of code based on whether
              its condition is <AstroCode
                code="true"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              /> or <AstroCode
                code="false"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              />.
            </p>

            <Code code={Figure1} lang="javascript" class="text-start" />
          </section>
          <section data-auto-animate>
            <h4>
              Components of an <AstroCode
                code="if"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              /> Statement
            </h4>
            <Code code={Figure1} lang="javascript" class="text-start" />
            <p class="fragment text-start">
              1. (<AstroCode
                code="if"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              />) if keyword - Denotes the beginning of an if statement.
            </p>
            <p class="fragment text-start">
              2. (<AstroCode
                code="age >= 16"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              />) Condition - A boolean expression that evaluates <AstroCode
                code="true"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              /> or <AstroCode
                code="false"
                lang="javascript"
                inline
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
              />.
            </p>
            <p class="fragment text-start">
              3. Code Block: A group of statements surrounded by braces.
              <AstroCode
                code={Figure2}
                lang="javascript"
                theme="material-theme-ocean"
                class="fragment"
              />
            </p>
